—ЩNarchive/external_nushell_repo_backup/nushell.github.io/commands/docs/length.mdЩ@4d6b33f9170d6a93afab38750858a1340d07e0c505cfc51c49f2231f70efccc1­title: length‘ЁExamplesЪqCount the number of items in a list
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> [1 2 3 4 5] | length
5

```
Count the number of rows in a table
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> [{a:1 b:2}, {a:2 b:3}] | length
2

```
Count the number of bytes in binary data
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> 0x[01 02] | length
2

```
Count the length a null value
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> null | length
0

```
